The Kano State Government has commenced  steps for the recruitment of 56 medical doctors with the conduct of aptitude tests for applicants shortlisted. The state said that this would  enhance the performances of  its Primary Healthcare Sector.   This is contained in a statement signed on Tuesday  by  Mr Maikudi Marafa, the Public Relations Officer of the state Primary Health Care Management Board . He  said that the board in the statement advised the applicants to be prepared for the challenges ahead.   ”The Executive Secretary of the  Board, Dr. Tijjani Hussain, urges the candidates to prepare for challenges.” Marafa quoted Hussain as saying that  successful candidates would be trained in: leadership, Data Management as well as  in the various Primary Healthcare activities.   Hussaini also  enjoined the applicants to be committed and  be dedicated to duty  after they would have been given employment. (NAN)